### TypeScript

TypeScript is a programming language that extends JavaScript with static type checking. It allows you to write code that is more robust and maintainable. TypeScript compiles your code into JavaScript, which means it runs on any browser or Node.js environment. It's known for its ability to catch errors early in the development process and provide a safer, more reliable development experience.

### Duck Typing

Duck Typing is a programming principle where you can use an object or function as long as it has a certain property or method that you expect. For example, if you have a function that takes an object as an argument, you can use it even if the object has a different structure or doesn't have some of the expected properties. This makes it more flexible and easier to work with objects that might have slightly different interfaces.

In essence, Duck Typing is about being more flexible and accepting that objects might have different structures or properties than what you initially expect.

